<br>
&quot;I mean, what the hell does Arwen (Liv Tyler) have to do in the damn book? They are making her more prominent to try and sell tickets because she is the only &quot;name&quot; star in the cast?&quot;<br>
<br>
I don't remember who said this, nor do I care. the &quot;name&quot; you have already been owned on, but for someone who has &quot;read the damn book,&quot; you sure don't know a lot about it.<br>
<br>
First off: buy The Silmarillion. Now. Right now.<br>
<br>
And if you already have it, read it. For real. Turn to page 380, in my version, and you see a family tree. You see &quot;Arwen == Aragorn.&quot; That little &quot;==&quot; means something.<br>
<br>
Then go to page 393. Look up &quot;Aragorn&quot; in the appendix of names. I'm quoting here: &quot;King of the reunited realms of Arnor and Gondor after the War of the Ring; wedded Arwen, daughter of Elrond.&quot;<br>
<br>
If you think you know anything about Middle Earth, but you haven't read The Silmarillion, you are so amazingly wrong. I'm not claiming to be the Jesus of Middle Earth, but this book will change everything you know about Tolkien. You find badasses who make Sauron look as evil as Darth Maul. Sure, he's bad - but there's worse.<br>
<br>
Oh, you want something outside of The Silmarillion? Something that, if you read the series, you should have picked up on?<br>
<br>
Page 280, last page of Chapter 5, &quot;The Steward and the King.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;...And Aragorn the King Elessar wedded Arwen Undoimiel in the City of the Kings upon the day of Midsummer, and the tale of their long waiting and labours was come to fulfilment.&quot;<br>
<br>
Page 381 in my version of Return of the King, it's toward the end of Appendix A, has a big heading: &quot;HERE FOLLOWS A PART OF THE TALE OF ARAGORN AND ARWEN.&quot; Good reading. <br>
<br>
&quot;...and [Aragorn] halted amazed, thinking he had STRAYED INTO A DREAM [emphasis mine], or else that he had received the gift of the elf minstrels, who can make the things of which they sing appear before the eyes of those that listen.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;strayed into a dream.&quot; Sound familiar? Watch The Two Towers again.<br>
<br>
&quot;...For a moment Aragorn gazed in silence, but fearing that she would pass away and never be seen again, he called to her, crying, Tinuviel, Tinuviel! egven as Beren had done in the Elder Days long ago.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;...But she laughed merrily and said: 'Then we are akin from afar. For I am Arwen Elrond's daughter, and am named also Undomiel.'<br>
    'Often it is seen,' said Aragorn, 'that in dangerous days men hide their chief treasure. Yet I marvel at Elrond and your brothers; for though I have dwelt in this house from childhood, I have heard no word of you. How comes it that we have never met before? Surely your father has not kept you locked in his board?'&quot;<br>
<br>
[...]<br>
<br>
&quot;Then Aragorn was abashed, for he saw the elven-light in her eyes and the wisdom of many days; yet from that hour he loved Arwen Undomiel daughter of Elrond.&quot;<br>
<br>
I know nobody wants to read more quoting and such, but, as you can see, I am a Tolkien fanboy. I'm more than a fanboy, I live this shit. I breathe this shit. I saw Fellowship as many times as was humanly possible. I expected to be disappointed, though.<br>
<br>
I wasn't.<br>
<br>
Now I know not everyone will like the movie, just like not everyone will like the books. C'est la vie. I don't really care.<br>
<br>
If it makes one person read the books, Peter Jackson did his job and deserved the money I gave him.<br>
<br>
But to say you don't see what Arwen had to do with the story, and then claim you read the books? My head hurts now.<br>
<br>
-Faldy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/blegacyofsteel43089.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tegian>Tegian</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/lonnelid/swedish.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/30/02 6:20:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3689.topic&index=32>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &gt;_&lt;</span><hr size=1> Yeah. The Aragorn / Arwen stuff isn't something Peter Jackson have pulled from thin air. It exists and I think Tolkien himself would like it.<br>
